title: net/rpc: document that Register logs to standard error
body:
by **thorduri@secnorth.net**: 
As noted in https://groups.google.com/forum/fromgroups=#!topic/golang-nuts/yzFYypD93nI
net/rpc's Register() will log.Println() a complaint
about methods that do not conform to the spec.


What steps will reproduce the problem?
1. http://play.golang.org/p/7ZHXj9tKLT

What is the expected output?
<no output>

What do you see instead?
2009/11/10 23:00:00 method F has wrong number of ins: 1

Which compiler are you using (5g, 6g, 8g, gccgo)?
6g

Which operating system are you using?
linux

Which version are you using?  (run 'go version')
go version go1.0.3
